nts1.d: Part of the NTS family since day dot, Moxie has held her Wednesday show since the stations first broadcasts. Inviting esteemed guests for interviews & mixes and breaking new, unreleased music, she’s got your Wednesday afternoons covered… Tune in to hear anything from Soulful House, Garage, Afro beats and all the way through to rolling techno.
After work fun and global tunes with Tash LC and guests every other Wednesday
Theo Motive takes you on a monthly journey through upfront Hip Hop, Beats, Grime, Bass & everything in between.

nts1.n: Steven Julien Presents: The Apron Show
nts1.d: The Apron Records boss takes his anything goes approach to an continually surprising hour of radio every month, featuring everything from dusty leftfield house to energetic jazz, and anything else that he's feeling.

nts1.n: MAXIMUM EXPOSURE POWER HOUR W/ TONY PRICE
nts1.d: Producer, DJ, L.I.E.S. Records recording artist and head of Maximum Exposure Inc.- Tony Price presents an action-packed mix of raw house, funk and freestyle recorded live in Greektown, Toronto..
London-based DJ Imogen takes on the NTS airwaves, bouncing between fuzzy electro and punishing techno.

NCA is a London tape label specialising in experimental, techno and hip-hop, co-run by Brassfoot. Tune in to his monthly NCA Show for exclusives and jams from across the range - techno, house, hip-hop and more…
Fusing the nostalgic, niche & the ‘nu A.G’. London’s best kept secret is back. Blends on brains off!

Two hours of powerful vocal performances and pop glamour from Illinois' "Queen of Funk". 
Selected by Emel.
From jazz, through field recordings to the threads of soundsystem - sonic imaginaries & memories once a month from Kast

Noise In My Head is a freeform sonic excursion presented by Melbourne based host Michael Kucyk. Over the years the show has been responsible for displaying talent from around the globe, from artists to DJs, label heads, compilation selectors and record collectors.
Leaf through songwriter Calvin LeCompte’s monthly selection via The Uline Catalog…

MAÏ-LINH - Tết Special: sounds from Vietnam

nts2.n: THE BADDIS SOUND W/ DANNIELLA DEE - Live from Vinyl Club Jamaica
nts2.d: Inspired by the iconic reggae & ska sounds of her home, singer & producer Danniella Dee shares a monthly crate of dub-wise selections, soul-soothing rocksteady, and heavyweight roots to the studio.
Tune into Martyn's monthly show on 2 for some delectable jazz treats from over the Atlantic.

Cultural critic and curator Timmhotep Aku explores the intersections of black music, life, metaphor, and meaning through songs and found audio footage.
From the host: "The emotions are mixed but my heart is pure. A soundtrack to my now as told through the music of Sun Ra, Roy Ayers, Roc Marci and more. Love to the world."

An exploration into obscure, underground, and lesser known music from Hawaii, bound not by genre or generation but by a connection to the islands. Hosted by Roger Bong of Aloha Got Soul, a record label and record store in Honolulu.
From the host: "Like a fever dream of free jazz, indie pop, ambient classical and other strange stuff."

nts2.n: THE WINDMILLS OF YOUR MIND w/ Taylor Rowley
nts2.d: DJ & music supervisor Taylor Rowley forages for the forgotten musical past every month, uncovering soundtracks, psych rock & other treasures.

nts2.n: SEA to SEA w/ Diana Ratsamee
nts2.d: Seattle DJ and collector Diana Ratsamee digs out musical discoveries from across the world, notably sharing music from Lao and Thailand and Southeast Asia - airing rock, disco, soul and psychedelic records, as well as diving into present day musical movements in the region.

The narrative is bursting with color and impossible to fit into a 60 minute timespan - but here is an effort to both timehop a personal story and nod to a timeless musical vignette of influences and inspiration that spans intensely amongst all corners of the artistic globe: shining bright into film + design + literature + circumstance as much as the sonic palette itself presents. Here’s a little exploration and adventure celebrating both the underbelly of the unknown with all that is beautifully pop.

nts2.n: bodies of divine infinite and eternal spirit
nts2.d: Selections from bodies of divine infinite and eternal spirit’ the experimental sound collective of rotating collaborators. They “aim to work against genre and toward surrender. playing improvisations, repetitions, spirituals, poetry, folk and obscurities.”

nts2.n: Mixed Fruit w/ Michael David (New Feelings)

nts2.d: KOTA from Stones Throw blends fresh new releases with timeless cuts across Soul, Beats, House and beyond — a two-hour journey recorded in Los Angeles.

nts2.n: Funk Freaks Radio w/ DJ Zee (R)
nts2.d: The notorious Orange County Funk Freaks crew take over the LA studio once a month with their signature brand of boogie, italo, and lowrider funk.

This hour of music moves through gospel, soul, and a spectrum of Black artists, tracing music as a spiritual architecture beyond the individual. Blending sacred textures with ambient and rhythmic passages, the episode explores sound as vibration , a living force shaped by Black Spirit.
Los Angeles native & synth pioneer Benedek blends ambient, boogie, funk & more, once a month from our LA studio.

subtle.d: With a monthly show on Subtle, Niceup is a London based DJ with a unique style. Pushing UKG, Breakbeat, Bass, Electro and 140. Weaving through genres showcasing new releases and older cuts.

Jedah started DJ'ing at the tender age of 18 years of age specialising in UK Garage/Grime. 

Jedah is currently the DJ for Grime Original Hollowman Jendor of the former Grime Collective Essentials/ OG's.

Responsible for “that massive grime tune with the Psycho strings”, UK producers/DJs Trends & Boylan are well versed in what the scene has to offer. They use this platform to showcase music from across the 140 spectrum from Grime to Dubstep. Anything goes!!

XOSÉ is a DJ and aspiring producer mixing and making mostly UK Garage, Grime and UK Funky. FORWARD PRESSURE largely focuses on the aforementioned UK born genres, though you can expect a variety of UK influenced sounds.

Sempra is a producer & DJ based in London, specialising in the fusion of UK Garage, Jungle and Breakbeat with dreamy vocal melodies and the beautiful instrumentation found in Soul and contemporary RnB. Sempra’s consistent output has been released by labels such as Future Classic and Headroom, gaining industry support from the likes of Nia Archives, Sherelle, Yung Singh and Dr Dubplate.

Cicely is a northern raised London based music photographer and DJ. From learning to mix during lockdown, she has since played at clubs across the country in venues such as Fabric, Corsica and Fold.

Cicely runs a collective and events night under the name NRG CRU which focus heavily on the high energy rave sound. She is highly influenced by the northern sound she grew up with, and you can hear this within her sets. Expect heavy blends of techno and hardcore while she shines the light on her favourite northern artists.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Bristol-born and London-based, Not Bad For A Girl resident DaiSu has been involved in the music scene since 2018 and has featured on stations such as Radio 1 Dance, BBC 6 Music and Melodic Distraction, as well as playing on line ups for Keep Hush, Skiddle and Red Bull. Her penchant for bass, breaks and 2-step has landed her gigs supporting acts such as Interplanetary Criminal, Main Phase, Craigie Knowes and Big Ang. In September 2022, her debut EP ‘Lightwork’ was released with Gather Records and was featured in DJ Mag's staff picks that same month.

Vinyl DJ from Leigh-on-Sea. Loves collecting records with a wide array of taste ranging from House and Techno to Grime, Dubstep and Jungle. Garage holds a special place in his heart and makes up the largest part of my collection and DJ sets.

DJ & Producer hailing from Watford influenced by Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Grime with releases on NSX records & Ghost Phone, spinning electronic genres from R&B edits, Drum and Bass and everything in between.
Highlander brings you 2 hours of the freshest Jungle, Hardcore, Dubstep and Breaks. 3rd Saturday 7-9pm lock in!

2Step Selects is a monthly show hosted by the Choki Biki Records crew. Founded in Dublin, Ireland, CBR consists of DJ Sharpson, 2step.png, Frame Shift, and MICK. The show consists of an all round breaks, electro, ukg and jungle hour, followed by an Irish showcase, demonstrating all the best Ireland has to offer collective/party/Dj & Producer wise!

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

subtle.n: The Ice Box Sessions with Frigid

subtle.d: Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

dublab.n: Carolina Isabel w/ Dro, Barlo & Niño Genisis – Una Noche Deep Cuts

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

dublab.n: Daddy Differently and Dirty Dave - Things of Life
dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
